TastyTrails Code of Conduct
Purpose
The TastyTrails community is committed to providing a welcoming, inclusive, and respectful environment for all contributors, regardless of level, background, or identity. This Code of Conduct outlines our expectations for participants to foster a positive collaborative experience.

Our Standards
All contributors to TastyTrails are expected to:

Be Respectful: Demonstrate kindness, empathy, and respect towards others.
Be Inclusive: Welcome everyone to participate, regardless of their skill level, background, or identity.
Be Collaborative: Work together effectively, support each other, and contribute to the project's growth.
Provide Constructive Feedback: Give feedback that is helpful, respectful, and specific, and be open to receiving feedback in return.
Avoid Discrimination and Harassment: Discrimination, harassment, bullying, or any offensive behavior is strictly prohibited.
Unacceptable Behavior
Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

Offensive or discriminatory comments, jokes, or insults.
Public or private harassment.
Posting inappropriate content.
Dismissing or belittling other contributorsâ€™ ideas or contributions.
Reporting and Enforcement

If you observe or experience any behavior that violates this Code of Conduct, please report it to the project administrators at [admin@tastytrails.com]. The project team reserves the right to remove, edit, or reject contributions that do not align with these standards or to ban any participant for inappropriate behavior.
